parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, which can be dangerous, especially in extreme weather conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
intermittent starting issues
power loss
security lock engages and prevents the vehicle from starting
delay in starting the vehicle after a short period of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passive lock sensor can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, which can be dangerous, especially in extreme weather conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
security lock engages and prevents the vehicle from starting
delay in starting the vehicle after a short period of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inline ignition fuse can cause the engine to stop and power steering to fail, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The inline ignition fuse keeps blowing
engine stops
power steering fails
no pattern to when it happens.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag warning system can cause the air bag indicator to remain illuminated, which can lead to accidents or injuries if the air bag does not deploy in a crash.
symptoms: Air bag indicator remains illuminated
air bag warning light stays on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the brake lights to not function, which can lead to rear-end crashes.
symptoms: Brake lights do not function
brake light switch failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of an accident, causing injuries or fatalities, or deploying unnecessarily, which can also cause injuries.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains on
the airbag does not deploy during an accident
the seat belt pre-tensioner is in a fault situation
broken wires in the wire harness to the extended cab rear door.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Pass Lock Security Feature Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the Pass Lock security feature can prevent the vehicle from starting, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing inconvenience or safety risks in emergency situations.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the security lock indicator on the dash flashes
the ignition key is not recognized
the vehicle starts after a delay of 10 minutes or more.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the engine to crank or start can cause inconvenience, delay, and potentially safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The engine fails to crank or start
no clicking or starting noises
all other electrical systems function normally
the vehicle starts after a delay of 20 minutes to an hour.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Timing Belt Stretching Causing Engine Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stretching of the timing belt can cause the engine to fail, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine fails to start
the vehicle is towed to a dealership
a new starter is installed.
